/**
* Options for default controls added to the map by default. Set to `false` to disable all map controls. Object
   * value is used to configure controls. See {@link https://openlayers.org/en/latest/apidoc/ol.control.html#.defaults}.
 * @type {(Object|boolean)}
   * @todo remove when vl-control-* components will be ready
 * @vueProp
 * @default true
 */
description: Options for default controls added to the map by default. Set to false to disable all map controls. Object value is used to configure controls. See {@link https://openlayers.org/en/latest/apidoc/ol.control.html#.defaults}.
todo: remove when vl-control-* components will be ready
name: controls

comment:
/**
* The element to listen to keyboard events on. For example, if this option is set to `document` the keyboard
   * interactions will always trigger. If this option is not specified, the element the library listens to keyboard
   * events on is the map target (i.e. the user-provided div for the map). If this is not `document` the target element
   * needs to be focused for key events to be emitted, requiring that the target element has a `tabindex` attribute.
 * @type {(string|Element|Document)}
   * @default undefined
 * @vueProp
 */
description: The element to listen to keyboard events on. For example, if this option is set to document the keyboard interactions will always trigger. If this option is not specified, the element the library listens to keyboard events on is the map target (i.e. the user-provided div for the map). If this is not document the target element needs to be focused for key events to be emitted, requiring that the target element has a tabindex attribute.
name: keyboardEventTarget

description: When set to true, tiles will be loaded during animations.
name: loadTilesWhileAnimating

description: When set to true, tiles will be loaded while interacting with the map.
name: loadTilesWhileInteracting

comment:
/**
* The map logo. If a **string** is provided, it will be set as the image source of the logo. If an **object** is provided,
   * the `src` property should be the **URL** for an image and the `href` property should be a **URL** for creating a link.
   * If an **element** is provided, the **element** will be used. To disable the map logo, set the option to `false`.
   * By default, the **OpenLayers** logo is shown.
 * @type {(string|Object|Element|boolean)}
 * @vueProp
 */
description: The map logo. If a string is provided, it will be set as the image source of the logo. If an object is provided, the src property should be the URL for an image and the href property should be a URL for creating a link. If an element is provided, the element will be used. To disable the map logo, set the option to false. By default, the OpenLayers logo is shown.
name: logo

comment:
/**
* The minimum distance in pixels the cursor must move to be detected as a map move event instead of a click.
   * Increasing this value can make it easier to click on the map.
   * @type {Number}
 * @vueProp
 * @default 1
 */
description: The minimum distance in pixels the cursor must move to be detected as a map move event instead of a click. Increasing this value can make it easier to click on the map.
name: moveTolerance

description: The ratio between physical pixels and device-independent pixels (dips) on the device.
name: pixelRatio

comment:
/**
* Renderer. By default, **Canvas** and **WebGL** renderers are tested for support in that order,
   * and the first supported used. **Note** that the **Canvas** renderer fully supports vector data,
   * but **WebGL** can only render **Point** geometries.
 * @type {(string|array)}
 * @vueProp
 * @default () => [RENDERER_TYPE.CANVAS, RENDERER_TYPE.WEBGL]
 */
description: Renderer. By default, Canvas and WebGL renderers are tested for support in that order, and the first supported used. Note that the Canvas renderer fully supports vector data, but WebGL can only render Point geometries.
name: renderer
